	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>14 Nover 1844</date></p>
				<p>My dear Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Business has brought me to <add>&#63;</add>&#44; and I<lb/> am therefore enabled to reply to your favor of <date>9 Oct</date> last.<lb/>  When I wrote to you about the spiced Beef&#44; I thought there<lb/> was some establishment in your city or in <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> for the putting up Beef for Exportation&#8212;If however<lb/> appears from your letter there is no such estbl.&#44; I shall<lb/> not therefore trouble you&#44; as I find I may be able to<lb/> procure the article as I cheap from <placeName>London</placeName>&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I notice with great attention your observation<lb/> on the state of Judaism in <placeName>America</placeName> &#38; your propose&#61;<lb/>tion to establish a Tract society for the benefit &#38; in<lb/>formation of the <hi rend="underline">poor</hi>.  But I am of opinion my<lb/> dear Friend&#44; that we should labour to excite the<lb/> minds of the wealthy &#38; bring them to a proper<lb/> sense of correctness&#44; when shall succeed in this&#44;<lb/> then of necessity will the poor follow the example<lb/> of those to whom they are in a great measure<lb/> indebted for their common means of support.<lb/>  This not to say the poor are ignorant&#44; but I tell you<lb/> the Rich are criminally so&#44; this by their example&#44;<lb/> of outrage against religious ordinances&#44; that the<lb/> poor follow&#44; &#38; when they see one who walks in a<lb/> high sphere of life violating these principles&#44; they<lb/> &#40;the poor&#41; <add>&#63;</add> <add>&#63;</add> of this as an excuse to <add>&#63;</add> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> their guilt.  I know it is so <hi rend="underline">here</hi>&#44; &#38; if any<lb/> opinion is not wrong&#44; then it is so in other places<lb/> I shall however think over this subject&#44; &#38; introduce<lb/> it to the consideration of our people here.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>I can hear nothing about the Book you state you have<lb/> sent me.  I fear the vessel was bound to <placeName><sic>Montigo</sic> Bay</placeName><lb/> thence it has not reached me.  Who did you direct<lb/> it to&#63;  Thus it is your Occidents are so long reaching<lb/> us&#8212;you should be more particular in your<lb/> information whenever you send us your works<lb/> or any other.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I send you a statement of our a&#47;c from last<lb/> settlement.  Namely</p>
				<p><date>Mar 1843</date></p>
				<table rows="8 " cols=" 2">
				<row>
				<cell>1 set Books sold for</cell>
				<cell>4.16.0 stg<add>&#63;</add></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 do extra bound...</cell>
				<cell>5. 8.0</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>2 setts Blinds....</cell>
				<cell>4. 4.0</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 set Books.....</cell>
				<cell>5. &#45;  &#45;</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>1 set Do <persName>Lopez</persName> ...</cell>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">4.16.0</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>
				<cell>24&#58;4&#58;0</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell>cash remitted acts 4 3 .....</cell>
				<cell><hi rend="underline">15</hi></cell>
				</row>
				<row>
				<cell/>    
				<cell><add>&#63;</add> 9&#58;4.0</cell>
				</row>
				</table>
				<p>This is the Bals<add>&#63;</add> I requested</p>
				<p><persName>Mr Peixotto</persName> to pay you for me.  <persName>Mr Joseph</persName> has<lb/> to settle for 1 set <hi rend="underline">you</hi> sent <hi rend="underline">him</hi>.  &#38; our set he<lb/> owes me for&#8212;Both of which he will arrange for<lb/> by flyer.  deducting duties paid &#38; 11&#36; advanced<lb/> poor <add>&#63;</add> <del>for</del> on same a&#47;c. also some of your<lb/> catechisms <hi rend="underline">he</hi> sold.  I have on hand for you<lb/> some of the Daily prayer Books&#44; I believe 2 <hi rend="underline">sets</hi><lb/> &#38; some of your other Books.  I gave over to <persName>DCordova</persName><lb/> your Sermons&#44; but I believe he has such done<lb/> much with them.  You can look into this<lb/> statement &#38; if there is any thing you wish<lb/> to be explained I will gladly do so.  Do not sup&#61;<lb/>pose I would sacrifice your Books&#44; I say so&#44;<lb/>  because you write&#44; &#8220;I hope the 41&#36; and are <hi rend="underline">not</hi><lb/> &#8220;all you have got for the 2 sets of prayer Books<lb/> &#8220;as that would be less than I sell them for here &#38;c<lb/> &#8220;&#38;c&#8221;</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>but I think you are thinking of the 2 sets I<lb/> offered to <persName>Rev Lindo</persName>&#8212;but which he did not take<lb/> if so you are in error&#44; &#38; you are richer in<lb/> Books here&#44; than you expected.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The &#8220;First Fruits&#8221; seem bl<add>&#63;</add>&#8212;you know<lb/> you already think I am <hi rend="underline">prejudiced</hi>&#44; therefore<lb/> I will be silent when <persName>Nathan</persName> is in question</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">God bless you&#44; &#38; keep you in his<lb/> keeping are the prayer of</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours Sincerely</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">M<add>&#63;</add> M Sollas</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Mr Alexr. Moralles</persName> mentioned to me<lb/> that he offered 2 &#189; &#36; when called to<lb/> Sepher in <placeName>Phda</placeName>&#44; which he left with<lb/> <persName>Mr. T. Tucker</persName> of <persName>Jas Barclay&#39;s</persName>&#44; <placeName>South<lb/> Wharfs</placeName>&#44; to hand over to you&#8212;if not<lb/> get paid&#44; please apply for it &#38;<lb/> let me know if its paid<add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">MS</persName></hi></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><persName role="author">M M. Sollis</persName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Kingston Ja</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Nov 14&#63;&#47;44</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">The <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">via&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName></p>
